<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17660514-31">
               <interp inst="t17660514-31" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17660514-31" type="year" value="1766"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17660514-31" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17660514"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17660514-31" type="date" value="17660514"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17660514-31-off184-c271" targOrder="Y" targets="t17660514-31-defend339 t17660514-31-off184 t17660514-31-verdict187"></join>
         
               <p>316. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17660514-31-defend339" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Harrison 
                  <interp inst="t17660514-31-defend339" type="surname" value="Harrison"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-defend339" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-defend339" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17660514-31-off184" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-off184" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-off184" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing six cart loads of gravel, value 12 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17660514-31-victim341" type="victimName">
                     Thomas 
                     Bird 
                  <interp inst="t17660514-31-victim341" type="surname" value="Bird"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-victim341" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-victim341" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17660514-31-off184 t17660514-31-victim341"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17660514-31-cd185" type="crimeDate">April. 17</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17660514-31-off184 t17660514-31-cd185"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17660514-31-person342">
                  Thomas 
                  Bird 
               <interp inst="t17660514-31-person342" type="surname" value="Bird"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-person342" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-person342" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 9th of April I had an account that the prisoner had taken some loads of gravel out of a pit in my field, and on the 17th I was informed by Mr. Wilkins he was then filling his cart of gravel at the same field, called <placeName id="t17660514-31-crimeloc186">Hornsey-field, in Islington</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17660514-31-crimeloc186" type="placeName" value="Hornsey-field, in Islington"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17660514-31-crimeloc186" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17660514-31-off184 t17660514-31-crimeloc186"></join> parish; he and I went and both saw him filling it; we followed him to the back of the Cock ale-house in Islington, there he shot it down; then I charged him with it; he pretended that he had that and others which he had sold of Mr. Barron.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17660514-31-person343">
                  Samuel 
                  Wilkins 
               <interp inst="t17660514-31-person343" type="surname" value="Wilkins"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-person343" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-person343" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             confirmed the account the prosecutor had given.</p>
               <p>Mr. Barron. The prisoner had no gravel of me on the 17th of April.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I do not deny but the gravel was from that field; my servant filled it to mend a skittle-ground with.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17660514-31-verdict187" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-verdict187" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-verdict187" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty, 10 d.
            </rs> 
                  <rs id="t17660514-31-punish188" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-punish188" type="punishmentCategory" value="corporal"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17660514-31-punish188" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="publicWhipping"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17660514-31-defend339 t17660514-31-punish188"></join>
               W
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
